The paper deals with error correction in random network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The concept of subspaces and their distances is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and coding theory (cs.CC). The study of maximal linear codes is also a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of linear algebra and combinatorics in the paper suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
